# Testing Rules

> **Auto-attached rationale:** @docs/workflows/03-qa-e2e.md
> (loads with this rule whenever you edit test files)

## Pyramid (respect the proportions)

- **Many** unit/use-case tests — fast, deterministic, ports replaced by fakes.
- **Some** integration tests — adapters against real boundaries.
- **Few** E2E (Playwright) — only critical user journeys.

Never invert it. E2E is expensive; reserve it for "if broken, the product is broken" paths.

## Rules

- Test behavior, not implementation. One focus per test.
- Every port has an in-memory **fake**; use it for unit/use-case tests.
- E2E selectors: `getByRole`/`getByText`, not brittle CSS/XPath.
- Tests are independent and idempotent — no shared mutable state, no order dependence.
- A user-visible bug fix ships with a regression test.

## AI in tests

- Use the **fake `AiProvider`** in unit and E2E — never a live model in CI.
- AI output *quality* is covered by evals ([evaluations.md](../../docs/ai/evaluations.md)), not E2E. E2E checks wiring only.

## Gate

- CI runs lint + unit + E2E smoke. Merge is blocked on red. Don't skip or weaken a test to go green —
  fix the cause.
